The family of Okonkwo Ebim Eke of Ndi Umozio of Ohafia Local government in Abia State, has announced the burial arrangement of their late mother, Madam Ogbonne Aja Eke Okonkwo for January 4th and 5th, 2021 . Late Madam Ogbonne Aja Eke Okonkwo passed on August 3, 2020 after a protracted illness. The deceased who died at the age of 77 years will be buried tomorrow, January 5th, in her home town. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! According to the family, a wake service will be held in her honor on today, Monday, Jan. 4th at NdiUmuozio compound, Abia State while the funeral service will held at Ofoaliagwu Primary School on Tuesday 5th. The Okonkwo Ebim Eke family in a statement signed by Onwuka Chuks said: “ In total submission, to the will of the Almighty God, we announce the glorious transition and the burial of our dear mother, sister, Aunty and grandmother who slept in the Lord after a long-time illness. May her gentle soul Rest In the bosom of the Lord,” the statement reads. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION